@Node "Starting QS-Edit" 

@{b}   STARTING QS-Edit@{ub}

 Just click QS-Edit icon or enter QS-Edit at CLI. But make sure these files 
 are in the same directory where you started QS-Edit from:

       -Keyboard.QS
       -Drums.QS
       -QS-Edit.prefs

@EndNode

@Node "Requirements"

@{b}   REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

       -At Least KS2.0 
       -Around 385Kb of chip memory, 445Kb memory of any type.
        Total 830Kb. SO ONE MEGA BYTE AT LEAST.
       -Processor 68000 -->
       -asl.library
       -serial.device, UNIT 0. These can be changed at the @{" Serial Prefs " Link "Prefs"} editor.
       
 Tested on A1200 KickStart 3.0 (39.106) with Blizzard 1230-III Turbo:

       -50Mhz 68030
       -50Mhz 68882 FPU
       -68851 MMU
       -32Mb of FAST RAM and 2Mb CHIP RAM.
@EndNode

@Node "Using QS-Edit" 

@{b}   USING QS-Edit@{ub}

    @{" READ THIS FIRST! " Link "Read this first"}
    @{" Menus " Link "Menus"}

@EndNode

@Node "Read this first" 

      THESE INSTRUCTINS ARE IMPORTANT TO READ FOR NOT LOOSING YOUR WORK!

 Before starting to use this software make backup of your synths data. For
 example with "SEND ALL DATA TO MIDI?" function found on your synth using
 some other software (like you sequencer). 

 Always when starting to edit a new program or loading program into memory  
 initialize all sounds on synthesizer. If you don't, synth may freeze up and
 display some error message. You can continue only by turning power off and 
 on again on synth. 

 Remember to press store button on synth after you have finished editing pr-
 ogram or mix!

 CHECK YOUR SYNTHESIZERS USER MANUAL IF YOU ARE UNFAMILIAR WITH INITIALIZING
 PROGRAM OR STORING PROGRAM/MIX.

@EndNode

