@Node "Control Sound"

 This window is where you can:

       -choose to edit KEYBOARD or DRUM parameters
       -enable or disable sounds 
       -change between different sounds
       -change between different drums (if in DRUM MODE)
       -flick between different KEYBOARD mode windows
@EndNode

@Node "Misc"

  This window is where you can edit:

-VOICE, LEVEL, PITCH, FILTER, and AMP/RANGE parameters.

  -Special notes about listview gadgets (those with what you choose sample 
   group/sample or modulation sources/destinations)!
      
       -Exit from listview gadget by pressing right mouse button and choose
        like normally with left mouse button.
       
       -You may have noticed these files Keyboard.QS and Drums.QS! If Not, 
        you find them from the same directory as where the main program is.
        They are normal ASCII files wich you can view with your text displa-
        yer/editor. This is where the sample group and sample names are sto-
        red for listview gadget. If you have sound card(s) you can change
        sample group and sample names to these files (Keyboard.QS for KEYB-
        OARD mode names and Drums.QS for DRUM mode names). 

        HERE IS HOW YOU DO IT!

        FIRST COPY FILES TO SOMEWHERE SAFE PLACE. IF YOU MANAGE TO MESS THE 
        FILES TOO BADLY YOU HAVE A BACKUP!!! 

        Start QS-Edit program and choose KEYBOARD or DRUM mode depending on
        which mode sound/group names you want to replace. Then press button:
            -'Voice...' at KEYBOARD mode 
            -'Sample Group... | Sample...' at DRUM mode
        Listview gadgets should pop in front now.   
          
        There are these weird group names 
            -CART 1...CART 8 and Grp 25...Grp 47 at KEYBOARD mode
            -CRT D1...CRT D6 and Grp 63 at DRUM mode
        Press one of those...
        
        If after selecting the group name there is reading something else in 
        synths display then in the selected name on computers screen you ha-
        ve found the right place where to start replacing with right names.
        Open your text editor and load either file. Find the group name from
        the first line, let's say it was CART 1 in KEYBOARD mode for exampl-
        e. Replace text CART 1 with the group name that is in the synth scr-
        een. Use only 6 letters for the name and leave one space mark, so 
        that there are total of 7 marks.

            ... CART 1 CART 2 CART 3 CART 4 ... the line is like this
            ... XXXXXX CART 2 CART 3 CART 4 ... change it to look like this
                      (replace the X marks with the name!!!)
                 REMEMBER TO LEAVE ONE SPACE MARK BETWEEN NAMES!! !

         And now let's replace those sample names. It's basically the same 
         thing but now you can use 10 letters for name and leave one space
         mark, total 11 marks.
         Find line which starts like this:

            offCART 1  n/a        n/a        n/a        ...

         And change n/a slots with the sample names and if you like, delete 
         the word CART 1 and leave word 'off' on it's place.

            off        XXXXXXXXXX XXXXXXXXXX XXXXXXXXXX ...

      I THINK YOU SHOULD UNDERSTAND IT NOW BUT READ THESE LAST WORDS!!!

  Pay attention to the space marks between names. If there are no space mar-
  ks (which stands for 0) QS-Edit program wont be able to lay the names cor-
  rectly in the listview gadgets. THE QS-Edit PROGRAM MAY EVEN CRASH. Espec-
  ially when changing last name in line be sure you don't leave too many or 
  any less marks.
@EndNode

