@Node "Mix"

@{b}   MODE MENU MIX@{ub}

 Here you can edit all the parameters found on MIX mode. Dragging sliders  
 and clicking cycle gadgets sends parameters to synth if serial (or similiar) 
 device opened properly. Gadgets also remember their values if you choose 
 different channels or change between different modes.

 On the bottom right corner there is MIX GROUP CHANNEL selector for QSR, I 
 don't know if this works on other synths. There is also cycle gadget to 
 activate GENERAL MIDI!
 
 The MIDI Group/Keyboard cycle gadget is named like that, because on QSR it 
 activates MIDI Group and on others the KEYBOARD. 
@EndNode

@Node "Prefs"

 Here you can select another device and different unit number. Also here are
 options to turn off parameter sending to synth after open!


 Open Device = if set, device is open and will be tried to opened when prog-
               ram is loaded. 

 Open Shared = If set, other programs can use the same device. If not, the 
               device is completelly at our use. Set this to off if you int-
               end to use the capture facility to be sure you don't loose 
               any data. 

 Unit        = defaults to 0, serial port found on every amiga. Other unit
               numbers are for extra ports added later to system with expan- 
               sion boards.

 Device Name = select another device for sending parameters to serial port. 
               Defaults to serial.device.

 Send To Synth After Open = if set, when you open project, parameters will 
                            be also send to synth. 

 USE         = use current settings 
 CANCEL      = exit without changing settings
@EndNode

@Node "ScrMode"

  Standard "ASL Screen mode requester" is used here to select different sc-
  reen modes. Graphic cards screen modes are also supported!

  NOTE!!!

  Never select screen mode lower than 640 x 256, expect trouble othervise! 
 
  Infact screen mode should be 640 x 256 because windows don't change in si-
  ze no matter how big screen mode you select! This is for clarity reasons.
@EndNode

@Node "LikeWB"

  When set on, screen just like workbench will be tried to open! When set  
  off, values from preferences will be used to open screen!

  Select your own screen mode to prefrences and save it!!! @{" Save Prefs " Link "SvPr"}
@EndNode

@Node "SvPr"

  Saves Serial and Screen Mode preferences to the same directory where you 
  started QS-Edit from! 
@EndNode
@Node "Play Controls..."

 If you don't have a keyboard and want to test modulation, pitchbend, aft-
 ertouch and velocity controllers effect on your programs and mixes.
 You can also play notes with these keys:

  2 3  5 6 7  9 0   = \     
 q w er t y ui o p [ ]
                              
  s d  g h j  l ;           
 z x cv b n m, . /


 There is also octave, notes off, program change and midi channel selectors.
 Octave can be changed by pressing F1 and F2, press SPACE to send notes off 
 message. 
@EndNode

@Node "Copy Sounds..."

 Here you can copy sounds to another sound or to buffer. If you want some 
 sound to another program: 

       - Copy it to buffer. 
       - Open another program. Maybe now you want to turn off the parameter
         sending to synth found on the @{" Serial Prefs " Link "Prefs"} editor.  
       - Select the same buffer as source and copy it to sound of your choi-
         ce.

 Parameters will also be send to synth.
@EndNode

@Node "INIT Sounds..."

 Here you can INIT parameters to match the values as if they vere INITiali-
 zed with synths controls. INIT can be done as KEYBOARD or DRUM init. This
 init actually only sends values to synth, which match the values if the so- 
 und would have been really initialized with synths controls manually.
   SO DON'T CONFUSE THIS WITH THE REAL INITIALIZE FOUND ON SYNTHS CONTROLS! 

 In KEYBOARD mode:

       - INIT SOUND = INITializes keyboard parameters from the current sound.
       - INIT DRUM  = is obsolete in this mode. 

 In DRUM mode:

       - INIT SOUND = INITializes all 10 drums parameters at the current so-
                      und.
       - INIT DRUM  = INITializes only parameters at the current drum.
@EndNode

@Node "Program Name..."

 Enter here name for your program. Use only the characters which are shown 
 in the window for avoiding problems. AND REMEMBER TO ALWAYS PRESS ENTER SO
 THAT THE CHANGES TAKE PLACE.

 Name will be printed at the screens title bar and send to synth. These same
 instructions apply also to mixes name found on @{" Mix " Link "Mix"} window.
@EndNode

@Node "Capture" 

@{b}   MODE MENU Capture@{ub}

    @{" READ THIS FIRST! " Link "Read This First!!!"}
    @{" Features " Link "Capture Mode Features"}
@EndNode


@Node "Read This First!!!"

    In this mode you can capture/dump SysEX messages via MIDI from your syn-
    thesizer. And you can copy parameters found on those dumps to editors.
    Capture is done automatically by first sending dump request message to
    synth. So you must only turn synth on and not needing to send message
    manually with "MIDI PRG", "MIDI MIX" or "SEND ALL DATA TO MIDI" functi-
    ons found on STORE mode. Of course this can be switched off if you want
    to dump data manually (ie. using some different synth model). Also there
    is the handy LISTVIEW gadget with what you can easily view ALL messages
    contents (explained on the "Capture Mode Features").

    MAYBE YOU SHOULD SET THE OPEN SHARED TO OFF WHEN USING THE CAPTURE FACI-
    LITY SO THAT THE DATA IS REALLY FROM THE SYNTH AND NOT FROM ANYWHERE EL-
    SE. SET IT TO OFF AT THE @{" Serial Prefs " Link "Prefs"} editor.
@EndNode

@Node "Capture Mode Features"

    Let's look at those gadgets found on the right side of the window first.

    NUMBER         = Select with this slider the PROGRAM+EFFECT or MIX that
                     you want to capture/dump from/to the "USER MEMORY". You
                     can select: 

                   - PRG+FX 0-127, MIX 0-99  
                   - And if you drag the slider all the way to right it sho-
                     uld say BUF on the place of the usual numbers. This me-
                     ans that you can also capture the EDIT BUFFER dependi-
                     ng of the CAPTURE MODE. You can also dump messages to
                     EDIT BUFFER with the same manner.

    CAPTURE MODE   = Select with this cycle gadget what you want to capture.
                     Possible modes:

                   - PROGRAM+EFFECT 
                   - MIX
                   - ALL

    CAPTURE        = IF YOU WANT TO CAPTURE PROGRAM+EFFECT CHANGE MODE WITH
                     SYNTHS CONTROLS TO 'PROG', AND IF MIX CHANGE IT TO 'MIX' 
                     THIS COULD HAVE BEEN DONE AUTOMATICALLY BY SENDING CHA-
                     NGE MODE MESSAGE TO SYNTH BUT I FOUND IT TO BE LITTLEB-
                     IT CONFUSING.
                     Start Capturing. After an succesful capture the bytes
                     that were captured are printed on the screen. And if c-
                     aptured an PROGRAM+EFFECT or MIX the name of it will a-
                     lso be printed so that you can be sure that you got the
                     right one. Capture can be stopped with ESC button. 

    AUTO CAPTURE   = In AUTO CAPTURE mode the capture is done automatically
                     by first sending an "dump request message" to synth on
                     which it will then respond with a dump depending of the
                     CAPTURE MODE.
                     Change this to MANUAL CAPTURE and you can capture mess-
                     ages by sending them manually with synths controls. 
    
    DUMP->SYNTH    = Click this button to dump message to synth. You can ch-
                     ange the memory location on which it will be sended wi-
                     th the NUMBER slider explained earlier. If you are dum-
                     ping PROGRAM+EFFECT an requester will ask you if you 
                     want to dump PROGRAM, EFFECT or BOTH parameters.

    COPY TO EDITOR = With this button you can copy parameters to PROGRAM+E-
                     FFECT or MIX editors depending of the message type. If
                     copying PROGRAM+EFFECT an requester will ask you if you
                     want to copy PROGRAM, EFFECT or BOTH parameters.

    CLEAR BUFFER   = Clears capture buffer so that another message can be
                     captured.

    YOU CAN ALSO ENTER THE CAPTURES SIZE MANUALLY BY CLICKING THE INTEGER
    GADGEDT WHICH SHOWS THE CAPTURE SIZE (491 for PROGRAM+EFFECT, 166 for
    MIX and 79479 for ALL). SO YOU CAN CAPTURE MESSAGES FROM OTHER MANUFACT-
    RES SYNTHESIZERS.  

    YOU CAN @{" SAVE " Link "Save As..."} MESSAGES TO DISK AND @{" OPEN " Link "Open..."} MESSAGES FROM DISK. 

    The LISTVIEW gadget found from the bottom right corner of the window.
    When captured or opened from an disk an ALL type of message, this gadget
    will be filled with the names contained by the message. First there are
    PROGRAM+EFFECT names and then MIX names. Every time you click on an name
    an operation defined by the cycle gadget under it will be done. The ope-
    rations:

    TEST PROGRAM/MIX   = PROGRAM+EFFECT or MIX will be send to synths EDIT
                         BUFFER, nothing will be changed from your synths m-
                         emories. This is an handy way to check what kind of
                         programs there are in that ALL message. 

    COPY TO EDITOR     = Copies parameters found on PROGRAM+EFFECT or MIX to
                         corresponding editor. If copying PROGRAM+EFFECT an 
                         requester will ask you if you want to copy PROGRAM,
                         EFFECT or BOTH parameters.

    COPY->SysEX EDITOR = Replaces ALL message with single PROGRAM+EFFECT or
                         MIX message at the capture buffer.

    SAVE PRG/MIX AS... = Saves one PROGRAM+EFFECT or MIX to disk.  

    I guess it's also nice to explain the large area where the numbers appe-
    ar when message is captured/opened. I added this that you can see easilly
    that capture was succesful. At least for now you can't edit those numbe-
    rs only view them and scroll the area with the scroller gadget.
    It is an custom to put those numbers as HEXADESIMAL. IF YOU DON'T KNOW 
    HOW TO READ THEM, IT SHOULD NOT MATTER. 
@EndNode

